dataframes = []
k_values = []
for archive in archives:
    df = archive_extraction.read_archive(archive, 'result.csv')
    df['mnk'] = df.m * df.n * df.k
    df['mn'] = df.m * df.n
    df['mk'] = df.m * df.k
    df['nk'] = df.n * df.k
    df['gflops'] = 2*df.mnk / df.duration * 1e-9
    k_val = df['k'].median().astype(int)
    df['k_val'] = k_val
    k_values.append(k_val)
    dataframes.append(df)

df = pandas.concat(dataframes)
print(len(df))
df.head()

df['cpu_id'] = 2*df['node'] + df['cpu'] - 2
for cpu in df['cpu_id'].unique():
    reg = stats[stats['cpu'] == cpu]
    assert len(reg) == 1
    reg = list(reg.iterrows())[0][1]
    df.loc[df['cpu_id'] == cpu, 'pred'] = reg['intercept']
    for prod in ['mnk', 'mn', 'mk', 'nk']:
        df.loc[df['cpu_id'] == cpu, 'pred'] += reg[prod] * df[df['cpu_id'] == cpu][prod]

def read_archive(archive, filename, time_margin=pandas.to_timedelta(0, unit='s')):
    df = archive_extraction.read_archive_csv(archive, filename)
    df['archive_name'] = archive
    info = archive_extraction.read_yaml(archive, 'info.yaml')
    df['expfile'] = info['expfile'][0]
    cluster = info['cluster']
    site = info['site']
    df['node'] = df['hostname'].str[len(cluster)+1:-(len(site)+len('..grid5000.fr'))].astype(int)
    df['timestamp'] = pandas.to_datetime(df['timestamp'])
    df['start'] = df['timestamp'] - df['timestamp'].min()
    exp_start = pandas.to_datetime(info['timestamp']['run_exp']['start'])
    exp_stop = pandas.to_datetime(info['timestamp']['run_exp']['stop'])
    df['in_exp'] = (df['timestamp'] > exp_start + time_margin) & (df['timestamp'] < exp_stop - time_margin) 
    return df

def my_melt(df, prefix, idcol):
    result = []
    columns = [col for col in df.columns if col.startswith(prefix)]
    for col in columns:
        tmp = df[idcol].copy()
        tmp[prefix] = df[col]
        tmp['group'] = int(col[len(prefix):])
        result.append(tmp)
    return pandas.concat(result)

frequency = my_melt(monitoring, 'frequency_core_', ['hostname', 'start', 'node', 'expfile', 'in_exp', 'k_val'])
frequency = frequency[frequency['group'] <= max(mapping.keys())]  # removing the cores with largest IDs (they are not real cores, just hyperthreads)
frequency['cpu'] = frequency.apply(lambda row: mapping[row.group], axis=1)
frequency['frequency_core_'] *= 1e-9
